parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to suddenly drop down or become stuck, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle. This can also compromise the security of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: The window suddenly drops down or becomes stuck
the window cable breaks or slips
the window cannot be rolled up or down
and the window makes a strange grinding or popping noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, which can lead to accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights do not operate unless the lever is held down constantly
and all lights go out on an intermittent basis.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires and explosions can cause serious injury or death, as well as significant damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: The engine caught on fire while the vehicle was turned on or parked

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaks in the intake manifold gasket can cause coolant to enter the engine, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially catastrophic failures.
Fuel system problems can cause engine stalling, hesitation, and poor performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Transmission problems can cause loss of power, hesitation, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Electrical system problems can cause engine stalling, hesitation, and poor performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Electrical system failures can cause various issues, including stalling, loss of power, and fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

symptoms: Windows not rolling up or down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failures can cause electrical system failures, stalling, and fires, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
